{"article_id":"5ySyHITqeRKQv8KB","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Republicans have no real plan","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"to establish a new health care system","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"if the courts strike down the Affordable Care Act before the 2020 election .","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"But plenty of them are rooting for its demise anyway","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"-","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"even if it means plunging the GOP into a debate","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"that splits the party","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"and leaves them politically vulnerable .","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"After a decade of trying to gut Obamacare ,","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"Republicans may finally get their wish thanks to a Trump administration-backed lawsuit .","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"Its success would cause chaos not only in the insurance markets but on Capitol Hill .","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"And Republican senators largely welcome it","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"-","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"even if they don ' t know what comes next .","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"\" I ' m ready for it to succeed , \"","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"said Sen. Mike Rounds","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"( R-S.D. ) .","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"\" I would love to get back in","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"and actually deal with health care again . \"","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"\" Do I hope","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"the lawsuit succeeds ?","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"I do , \"","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"said Sen. Kevin Cramer","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"( R-N.D. ) .","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"\" What I wish is we had some idea","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"where we are going","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"if it does succeed ,","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"as it looks more and more like it might . \"","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"Even Republicans","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"not known for taking a hard line","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"are eager for a forcing mechanism","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"to take on Obamacare .","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"\" I have a plan","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"that I would be delighted to have Congress pick up and go forward with , \"","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"added Sen. Mitt Romney","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"( R-Utah )","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"of a proposal","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"to protect pieces of the law .","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"\" Necessity is the mother of acceptance .","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"I hope","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"that we reach that necessity","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"and that would propel my proposal to see a good deal of support . \"","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"Both Cramer and Romney said","depth":6},{"id":43,"text":"GOP discussions were picking up","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"about how to step in","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"if the law falls","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"after a U.S. appeals court indicated last week","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"it could kill all or part of the law ,","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"though the Supreme Court would have the final say .","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"Democrats and Republicans are also working on a modest package of bills","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"intended to lower health care costs .","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"But","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"when it comes to major changes to Obamacare ,","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"the parties aren ' t talking .","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"Democratic leaders have no intention","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"of working with the GOP","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"since they want the Affordable Care Act to survive .","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"And there ' s no reason","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"to think","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"that Senate Republicans could unify on a replacement to the law","depth":12},{"id":60,"text":"after previously failing to do so .","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"\" If it did succeed ,","depth":12},{"id":62,"text":"I would be very concerned , \"","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"said Sen. Susan Collins","depth":13},{"id":64,"text":"( R-Maine )","depth":13},{"id":65,"text":"of the lawsuit .","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"\" I don ' t think","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"there ' s a plan in place","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"to take care of individuals","depth":14},{"id":69,"text":"who ' ve been using the exchanges","depth":16},{"id":70,"text":"to purchase their insurance","depth":16},{"id":71,"text":"or who have been covered under the Medicaid expansion .","depth":15},{"id":72,"text":"I ' m just hoping","depth":12},{"id":73,"text":"the court doesn ' t strike it down . \"","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"Democrats are ready to hammer Republicans","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"if the law gets taken down","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"because of the GOP lawsuit .","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"Democrats took back the House last year","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"in large part because of their focus on health care .","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"Senate Minority Leader Chuck Schumer","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"( D-N.Y. )","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"called the GOP ' s stance \" repeal without a replace . \"","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"\" Every plan","depth":14},{"id":83,"text":"Republicans have put forward","depth":14},{"id":84,"text":"has failed to maintain the protections","depth":14},{"id":85,"text":"offered under the current law , \"","depth":14},{"id":86,"text":"he said .","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"\" It 's pretty simple :","depth":12},{"id":88,"text":"If you care about maintaining protections for people with preexisting conditions ,","depth":13},{"id":89,"text":"you don ' t demand","depth":14},{"id":90,"text":"they be taken away . \"","depth":14},{"id":91,"text":"Sen. Joe Manchin","depth":12},{"id":92,"text":"( D-W.Va. ) ,","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"a close Schumer ally , added ,","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"\" They better do something .","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"If not ,","depth":12},{"id":96,"text":"this is all on them .","depth":13},{"id":97,"text":"This is all on Mitch McConnell . ''","depth":13},{"id":98,"text":"Republicans may be wagering","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"that Democrats would jump into negotiations","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"to protect popular provisions in Obamacare","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"and somehow forge a new compromise health care law","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"- all in the heat of the presidential campaign .","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"( R-Ky. )","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"has said","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"Congress would act immediately on pre-existing conditions","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"if the courts strike down that part of the law .","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"But it ' s also possible that the law would simply collapse","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"and Congress play a blame game for months","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"as millions of Americans struggle to deal with the fallout .","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"Republican efforts","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"to create a new law","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"fell short in 2017 ,","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"and Democrats are not exactly unified on whether to protect Obamacare or embrace a larger role for government like with \" Medicare for All . \"","depth":8},{"id":115,"text":"It ' s difficult , if not impossible , to see how the parties would compromise a year from now .","depth":7},{"id":116,"text":"McConnell quickly shied away from President Donald Trump ' s talk","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"of restarting efforts","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"to replace the law","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"earlier this year ,","depth":8},{"id":120,"text":"and in May said ,","depth":8},{"id":121,"text":"\" It ' s not possible \" to reconcile the GOP ' s priorities with Speaker Nancy Pelosi ' s on a major replacement bill .","depth":8},{"id":122,"text":"In interviews , several Senate Republicans insisted","depth":9},{"id":123,"text":"that Congress could get its act together .","depth":9},{"id":124,"text":"But veterans of the health care wars are not so sure .","depth":9},{"id":125,"text":"Sen. Lisa Murkowski","depth":14},{"id":126,"text":"( R-Alaska ) ,","depth":14},{"id":127,"text":"who killed the GOP ' s repeal push with Collins and the late Sen. John McCain ,","depth":13},{"id":128,"text":"observed dryly of the efforts","depth":13},{"id":129,"text":"to replace Obamacare :","depth":13},{"id":130,"text":"\" You know","depth":12},{"id":131,"text":"how much I loved that fight . \"","depth":12},{"id":132,"text":"Sen. Shelley Moore Capito","depth":15},{"id":133,"text":"( R-W.Va. ) ,","depth":15},{"id":134,"text":"who voted with her party in 2017 on the so-called \" skinny repeal \" ,","depth":14},{"id":135,"text":"signaled","depth":13},{"id":136,"text":"she was also eager to avoid another wide-ranging health care debate .","depth":12},{"id":137,"text":"\" I can ' t say","depth":14},{"id":138,"text":"that I hope","depth":15},{"id":139,"text":"it succeeds , \"","depth":15},{"id":140,"text":"she said of the lawsuit .","depth":13},{"id":141,"text":"\" I think","depth":14},{"id":142,"text":"the strategy from here on that","depth":17},{"id":143,"text":"I ' ve adopted in my own mind","depth":17},{"id":144,"text":"is repair .","depth":16},{"id":145,"text":"Repair what we ' ve got. \"","depth":15},{"id":146,"text":"She then pivoted into a GOP line","depth":15},{"id":147,"text":"that will be heard for months :","depth":15},{"id":148,"text":"\" You know ,","depth":16},{"id":149,"text":"you see the Democrat presidential candidates .","depth":16},{"id":150,"text":"They want to scrap it , their own creation . \"","depth":15},{"id":151,"text":"The Democratic focus","depth":10},{"id":152,"text":"on moving beyond Obamacare","depth":11},{"id":153,"text":"- either through Medicare for All or through proposals","depth":12},{"id":154,"text":"to let people buy into Medicare -","depth":12},{"id":155,"text":"could further complicate any effort by Congress","depth":9},{"id":156,"text":"to react to a potential Supreme Court ruling","depth":9},{"id":157,"text":"that strikes down Obamacare , a decision","depth":10},{"id":158,"text":"that may occur next year","depth":11},{"id":159,"text":"if the appeals court shoots down the law in the coming months .","depth":11},{"id":160,"text":"The lawsuit","depth":10},{"id":161,"text":"backed by GOP attorneys general , the Trump administration and many GOP lawmakers","depth":10},{"id":162,"text":"argues","depth":9},{"id":163,"text":"that the Affordable Care Act should collapse","depth":10},{"id":164,"text":"now that Congress has zeroed out its individual mandate in a Republican tax law .","depth":10},{"id":165,"text":"A previous Supreme Court ruling had used the mandate as reason","depth":10},{"id":166,"text":"to uphold the law .","depth":10},{"id":167,"text":"Collins said","depth":9},{"id":168,"text":"she viewed the case as clear-cut :","depth":9},{"id":169,"text":"Congress ' failure","depth":10},{"id":170,"text":"to repeal the entire law in either a standalone bill or the tax law","depth":10},{"id":171,"text":"is evidence","depth":10},{"id":172,"text":"that lawmakers were focused only on the mandate in the tax bill .","depth":10},{"id":173,"text":"Sign up here for Huddle","depth":4},{"id":174,"text":"A daily play-by-play of congressional news in your inbox .","depth":4},{"id":175,"text":"Email Sign Up","depth":5},{"id":176,"text":"By signing up","depth":7},{"id":177,"text":"you agree to receive email newsletters or alerts from .","depth":7},{"id":178,"text":"You can unsubscribe at any time .","depth":6},{"id":179,"text":"This site is protected by reCAPTCHA","depth":5},{"id":180,"text":"and the Google Privacy Policy and Terms of Service apply .","depth":5},{"id":181,"text":"For Sen. Ron Johnson","depth":6},{"id":182,"text":"( R-Wis. ) ,","depth":6},{"id":183,"text":"the collapse of Obamacare in the courts \" would be a relief . \"","depth":5},{"id":184,"text":"\" I would anticipate","depth":6},{"id":185,"text":"that the court would give a certain level of time","depth":8},{"id":186,"text":"for Congress to get its act together in a way","depth":9},{"id":187,"text":"that actually works , \"","depth":9},{"id":188,"text":"Johnson said .","depth":7},{"id":189,"text":"\" We ' re not going to turn the switch on right away ,","depth":6},{"id":190,"text":"but doesn ' t hurt to have a deadline . \"","depth":6},{"id":191,"text":"Yet Republicans also admit","depth":6},{"id":192,"text":"the lawsuit has the potential","depth":7},{"id":193,"text":"to be politically damaging , not just to Trump but to their Senate majority .","depth":7},{"id":194,"text":"Republicans are fighting a pitched battle","depth":8},{"id":195,"text":"to defend their 53-47 majority ,","depth":8},{"id":196,"text":"and polls show","depth":8},{"id":197,"text":"Democrats have the high ground on health care amid GOP efforts","depth":9},{"id":198,"text":"to dismantle the Affordable Care Act .","depth":9},{"id":199,"text":"\" I only fear the political consequences of \" false Democratic attacks ,","depth":9},{"id":200,"text":"said Sen. Mike Braun","depth":11},{"id":201,"text":"( R-Ind . ) ,","depth":11},{"id":202,"text":"who backs efforts","depth":11},{"id":203,"text":"to protect pre-existing conditions .","depth":11},{"id":204,"text":"He said","depth":9},{"id":205,"text":"he worried","depth":10},{"id":206,"text":"Democrats might not join efforts","depth":12},{"id":207,"text":"to prop up those protections \" for some technicality","depth":12},{"id":208,"text":"just so they can keep coming at us for the lawsuit. \"","depth":11},{"id":209,"text":"But Republicans conceded","depth":8},{"id":210,"text":"that","depth":9},{"id":211,"text":"if they don ' t begin preparing for the potential maelstrom","depth":11},{"id":212,"text":"their party has created ,","depth":11},{"id":213,"text":"it will be their own fault .","depth":10},{"id":214,"text":"\" That people are concerned about losing the Affordable Care Act is testament to the fact","depth":7},{"id":215,"text":"that the United States Congress hasn ' t done its job , \"","depth":7},{"id":216,"text":"said Sen. John Kennedy","depth":8},{"id":217,"text":"( R-La . ) ,","depth":8},{"id":218,"text":"who is \" ready \" for the lawsuit to succeed .","depth":7},{"id":219,"text":"Obamacare has \" not made their lives better ,","depth":6},{"id":220,"text":"but yet people worry","depth":7},{"id":221,"text":"that","depth":8},{"id":222,"text":"as bad","depth":10},{"id":223,"text":"as it is ,","depth":10},{"id":224,"text":"if we don ' t have it ,","depth":10},{"id":225,"text":"we have nothing . \"","depth":10}],"relations":[{"parent":451,"left":398,"right":450,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":398,"left":233,"right":397,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":233,"left":228,"right":232,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":228,"left":227,"right":2,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":227,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":232,"left":3,"right":231,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":231,"left":4,"right":230,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":230,"left":5,"right":229,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":229,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":397,"left":273,"right":396,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":273,"left":252,"right":272,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":252,"left":235,"right":251,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":235,"left":234,"right":10,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":234,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":251,"left":237,"right":250,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":237,"left":11,"right":236,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},